"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In responding, I have taken each of the key areas identified in your invitation for submissions.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:25.34pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="display:none; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.0.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The effectiveness of C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ommissioners in reducing crime and delivering an effective police service within their police force area</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Police and Crime P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">lan I </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">developed aims to empower police and other agencies to work together to build safer communities in Greater Manchester. In an era of austerity, with </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">significant</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> cuts to the police service and other bodies, working in partnership</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> with other agencies</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> is key to delivering effective policing</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and safer communities</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. I have been able to bring partnership agencies toge</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ther in a way that simply did not</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> happen before I was elected. Complex issues such as child sexual exploitation or domestic violence are challenges the police </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cannot</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> deal with on their own. And this is where Commissioners can be pivotal. Having one local, democratically-accountable figure who takes a strategic view across both the criminal justice system and the community safety agenda, who brings different agencies together around the table to find better ways of working, is central</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to improving confidence in police and other agencies, and making our communities safer</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. And here in Greater Manchester, this </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">is not just a talking shop – we are</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> delivering real change for the people I represent.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The neighbourhood policing model also sits at the heart of delivering effective policing, and this is something that the Chief Constable and I are determined to ensure remains embedded into the culture and practice of GMP. I used</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> modest increase in the police precept (10p per week for the average bill) to support the frontline. The £3.3m generated from the precept increase has been used to bolster neighbourhood policing, creating new neighbourhood police </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">officers and support staff.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I have</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> also introduced new ways of holding the police to account. For a long time the target culture </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">was the main way in which police performance could be measured. I believe this is a flawed model, and have</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> done away with </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">targets</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, preferring instead new, meatier performance reports taking a more rounded view. We examine </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">what crimes are going up, what is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> going down and what the trends are. This helps identify areas where more work is needed and is much more effective than a targets regime. It’s intelligent monitoring of intelligent policing.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Alongside this new way to monitor performance, I have introduced parliamentary-style forums which take a detailed look at issues of significant public interest</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (see below)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. I hav</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e also ensured that the public gets regular opportunities to question directly the Chief Constable and me, for example at public meetings, which I have held throughout Greater Manchester since being elected.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:25.34pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="display:none; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3.0.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The role of C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ommissioners in holding their </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Chief C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">onstables to account</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">As outlined above, the new style of forum allows the Chief Constable and relevant </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">senior </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">officers and staff to be questioned in detail on issues of significant public interest. Topics we have looked at so far include fraud, police standards and domestic violence and those giving evidence have been questioned not just by me and my deputy, but a by a range of pane</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">lists from different walks of life and political persuasions.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">As another</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> example, I recently extended the Chief Constable’s contract for three years and at one of these public forums </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I asked him to outline</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> his vision for GMP in the coming years. He was then questioned by a panel that included journalists, community representatives </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">and the leader of Rochdale Council, who also chairs the Police and Crime Steering Group (see below)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">3.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">For performance measurement, in addition to the new-style performance reports which look at GMP as a whole, I recently published similar reports for each of the districts of Greater Manchester. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This gives residents the chance to see how police are performing in their own district, in addition to at a Greater Manchester level.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:25.34pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="display:none; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.0.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The role of P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">olice and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Crime P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">anels in holding their C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ommissioners to account</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In Greater Manchester the Police and Crime Panel comprises the nine local authority leaders, Salford City Mayor and two independent members. The seniority of the membership demonstrates how Greater Manchester local authorities value the Commissioner’s role, and demonstrates their commitment to the community safety agenda.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Underpinning the P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">anel is a separate </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Steering G</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">roup which works with my office, po</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">lice and partner agencies. The Steering G</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">roup conducts specific pieces of joint work</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> with police, my office and other agencies. F</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">or example</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, the G</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">roup has secured agreement between police and the 10 local authorities on charging for events on the highway. Shortly it will be working on a shared approach to dealing with domestic violence</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">. This allows the P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">anel to concentrate on setting a strategic</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> direction for local authority Crime and Disorder P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">artnerships, and focus on scrutinising my work.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I believe the model adopted here in Greater Manchester is the right one. The seni</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ority of the membership of the P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">anel allows it to be a truly strategic group, which can also </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">scrutinise</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> my work with authority. Having a d</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">elivery group underpinning the P</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">anel’s strategic overview creates opportunities for further joint working, and – as has been seen here in Greater Manchester – allows for a consensus to be built on issues where agreement has</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> previously</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> been challenging. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I believe the role of Police and Crime Panels should be reviewed and enhanced. The ultimate sanction against any Commissioner is, of course, the ballot box and it is entirely appropriate that the final say should be the public’s. But there should be further checks and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">balances in the system to hold C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ommissioners to account who are not performing or who have strayed vastly from their manifesto. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">4.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">This </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cannot</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> be used as a way of settling political grudges or playing party politics. A sensible option would be to have a recall function. But this would need to be underpinned by a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">real, and not synthetic, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">public appetite, perhaps being activated by public petition</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> with a clear minimum threshold</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, and must not undermine the democr</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">atic legitimacy of the elected C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ommissioner.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:25.34pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="display:none; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.0.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The division </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">of functions and staff between Commissioners and C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">hief </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">onstables following the Stage 2 transfers under the Police Reform and</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> Social Responsibility Act 2011</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I have worked closely with GMP to ensure a smooth transfer of staff. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have agreed with GMP that all staff will transfer to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">the Chief Constable from April.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:25.34pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="display:none; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">6.0.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The role of C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ommissioner</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">s in budget and precept setting</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">As outlined above, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">there are significant pressures on police budgets. Greater Manchester Police has</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> lost more than 1,000 officers . By 2016 that will have risen to nearly 2,000. By 2017, more than £137m will have been cut from GMP’s budget. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In this challenging climate we have to prioritise and that is why I have focused this year’s precept increase on bolstering neighbourhood policing. This model of policing is a real success story, and both the Chief Constable and I are determined to do all we can to ensure it continues. We cannot return to an era of blue light police response. Neighbourhood policing teams are part of the fabric of communities across Greater Manchester, driving up confidence and helping to keep crime down. By asking for a small additional contribution from the public, we have been able to help secure the neighbourhood policing model.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Within the budget I have also sought where possible to encourage partnership working and funding innovative schemes to reduce demand on police and improve services to victims. So GMP and the NHS are currently running a pilot scheme where there will be immediate and better sharing of information and expertise when police are called to an incident involving an individual with mental health problems. This has been funded from money I have set aside to target mental health and the drain it puts on police resources. As this kind of scheme b</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ears fruit, I am</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> confident we can pool more resources with other agencies to try and improve services in a context of shrinking resources.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">6.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Similarly, I have worked with Victim Support and the NHS to develop a groundbreaking initiative to help get targeted support to victims of domestic violence quickly and at a much earlier point. Domestic abuse specialists will be based in Accident and Emergency units to help NHS staff identify victims domestic violence when they present at hospital and get those victims quickly and appropriately referred to support services.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:25.34pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="display:none; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">7.0.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The effectiveness of C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ommissioners in promoting local policing priorities</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">My role </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">cannot</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> be one where I sit in an of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">fice all day long. I have</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> been elected by the people of Greater Manchester and it is really important that I </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">regularly </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">meet as many members of the public </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">as possible.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> So I ensure that </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I regularly visit </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">HomeWatch</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> groups, victims’ groups, major events, formal public meetings, community projects and other events that allow me to meet the public, listen to their concerns and ideas and respond to them.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In addition, I have a strong presence on social and new media platforms, regularly participating in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">webchats</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and responding to questions that have been raised online.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">7.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I also generate s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ignificant media coverage and engagement with local media</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> with regular columns in the main papers, and appearances on media outlets. We have also worked in partnerships with the media to get messages out on major issues. For example, in November I ran an awareness month for domestic abuse to get the message out to the public that help is out there for victims and their families.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> This was aimed at combating low levels of reporting domestic violence, demonstrating clearly that police and other agencies will take domestic violence seriously, thereby building confidence for those experiencing it, and demonstrating that we all have a part to play in changing the climate of acceptance that still exists within society generally.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:25.34pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="display:none; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">8.0.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Progress on establishing colla</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">boration agreements with other C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ommissioners, policing organisations and partners</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I work closely, and have a good</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> relationship, with all of the C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ommissioners in the North West, meeting regularly and looking for opportunities to work together. For larger forces, collaboration benefits can be more effectively leveraged by </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">working with other agencies within </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">our area, rather than formal agreements with other forces. So, for example, we are developing collaboration agreements on things like design and print services and fleet management with Manchester City Council. There are significant opportunities available to work more closely with local authorities on a range of issues from human resources to finance which I am seeking to develop in the coming year. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">8.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">However</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, effective collaboration does not</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> necessitate formal agreements. Informal arrangements can be just as powerful. For example, we have seen the benefits of co-locating council, police and other services in the same building, creating a new way of working that not only drives modest financial savings, but actually helps in the delivery of a better service. I am also developing a local victims’ charter with the rest of the criminal justice system partner agencies in Greater Manchester which will sit alongside the national code, but will be more user-friendly and accessible.   </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.36pt; padding-left:25.34pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="display:none; font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">9.0.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Tr</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ansparency of and reporting by C</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ommissioners to date.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt; text-indent:-38.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">9.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">It should go without saying that any elected representative should be committed to transparency – I am here to represent the people of Greater Manchester and they must be able to see that I am representing them well. All of the information that I am required to publish is on my website and is easily accessible through a simple search function.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:14pt">Tony Lloyd</span><br /><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:14pt">Police and Crime Commissioner for </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:14pt">Greater Manchester</span><br /><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:14pt">December 2013</span></p><p style=